There are multiple great resources on the internet about using Node, but sometimes they can be hard to find. It&#39;s even harder to find resources about how to get started for an absolute beginner.

[This YouTube video](https://youtu.be/U8XF6AFGqlc?t=560) is very informative without too much fluff and shows how to get started from nothing. (The hyperlink timestamp starts at 9:20 which is when the actual programming begins, but the first part of the video is informative as well)

After that video, the same YouTuber has a [playlist where he makes a wesbite using Node, Express and Pug](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLillGF-RfqbYRpji8t4SxUkMxfowG4Kqp) which you can watch to understand how to set up your back-end server and then you can utilize the code at the top portion of this answer!

